.SH NAME
wait_for_completion \- - waits for completion of a task
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" wait_for_completion
.BI "(struct completion *x "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "x" 12
holds the state of this particular completion
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This waits to be signaled for completion of a specific task. It is NOT
interruptible and there is no timeout.

See also similar routines (i.e. \fBwait_for_completion_timeout\fP) with timeout
and interrupt capability. Also see \fBcomplete\fP.
